\pard\qc\sa240\f0\fs34\b THOG2 Principled Compact Geometry Implementation Plan\b0\par
\pard\qc\sa320\f0\fs22 CURVE, MLP_BLOCK, BLOCK, HEAD_AWARE_BLOCK, CHEBY, and DCT\par

\pard\sa190\sb280\f0\fs29\b Summary\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 This plan implements the accepted clean-axis compact geometry spec in small, testable stages.\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 The first priority is not new geometry. The first priority is a clean abstraction seam that preserves DENSE and proves legacy CHEBY_SHEET_COL equivalence.\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 After that seam exists, implementation proceeds through CURVE, MLP_BLOCK, HEAD_AWARE_BLOCK, BLOCK, and then DCT.\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 MLP_BLOCK should land before HEAD_AWARE_BLOCK because MLP matrices dominate repeated transformer matrix parameters.\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 BLOCK is a user convenience preset. It should be implemented only after both underlying module geometries work independently.\par

\pard\sa190\sb280\f0\fs29\b 1. Working rules\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 Preserve existing working code paths until equivalence tests prove the replacement path.\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 Do not silently reinterpret old compact checkpoints. Missing or mismatched compact metadata must hard-fail.\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 Keep nanoGPT execution compatibility at the boundary. Do not let nanoGPT packing tensors define compact parameter families.\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 Treat Q, K, V, and attention output as semantic families. Concatenate Q/K/V into c_attn only after materialization.\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 Treat attention head index as categorical. Do not build a compact basis over head index.\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 Keep LayerNorm, biases, embeddings, and lm_head out of scope for this enhancement.\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 Mark code changes according to the THOG source marking convention. Do not delete original nanoGPT lines when replacing a working path; comment them out or isolate the new path cleanly.\par

\pard\sa190\sb280\f0\fs29\b 2. Target config surface\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 Add explicit compact identity fields.\par
\pard\sa180\li360\f1\fs20 geometry_preset = curve | mlp_block | block\line attention_geometry = curve | head_aware_block\line mlp_geometry = curve | mlp_block\line basis_family = chebyshev | dct\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 Preset expansion must be deterministic.\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 CURVE resolves to attention_geometry=curve and mlp_geometry=curve.\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 MLP_BLOCK resolves to attention_geometry=curve and mlp_geometry=mlp_block.\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 BLOCK resolves to attention_geometry=head_aware_block and mlp_geometry=mlp_block.\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 Explicit module-level overrides must remain available for ablations.\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 New run names and manifests should include the preset and the resolved module geometries.\par

\pard\sa190\sb280\f0\fs29\b 3. Stage 0: audit and baseline fixtures\b0\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Goal\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 Lock down what the current code does before changing abstractions.\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Work items\b0\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Inspect sheet/model.py, sheet/trajectory.py, sheet/geometry.py, sheet/basis.py, train.py, and current wrapper scripts.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Record current legacy CHEBY_SHEET_COL coefficient shapes and parameter counts.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Record current materialized tensor shapes for c_attn, attention output, MLP expansion, and MLP contraction.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Add a deterministic fixture that materializes one or more current compact matrices from fixed seed/config.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Add a small audit note documenting current head packing for Q/K/V and attention output.\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Exit gate\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 Existing DENSE and compact smoke tests pass. A fixed legacy CHEBY_SHEET_COL materialization fixture exists.\par

