\pard\sa190\sb280\f0\fs29\b 5. Stage 2: basis-kernel interface with CHEBY only\b0\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Goal\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 Move current Chebyshev basis construction behind a modular basis-kernel interface without changing numerical output.\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Likely files\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 sheet/basis.py and new helper files if useful, such as sheet/basis_kernels.py.\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Work items\b0\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Define a basis kernel object or registry.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Move Chebyshev coordinate policy, recurrence, and QR stabilization into the CHEBY kernel.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Include basis_family and basis_version in cache keys.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Keep basis tensors non-persistent and out of optimizer groups.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Keep the current basis version string for CHEBY unless a deliberate version bump is needed.\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Tests\b0\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - CHEBY basis equality against the pre-refactor fixture for fixed sample_count, order, dtype, and device.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Shape, dtype, device, cache, non-persistence, and Gram-error tests.\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Exit gate\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 CHEBY basis behaviour is numerically preserved. No DCT code exists yet.\par

\pard\sa190\sb280\f0\fs29\b 6. Stage 3: semantic families and materialization seam\b0\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Goal\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 Separate semantic tensor families from nanoGPT packed tensors, while still proving legacy CHEBY_SHEET_COL equivalence.\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Likely files\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 sheet/geometry.py, sheet/trajectory.py, sheet/model.py, and tests.\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Work items\b0\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Define semantic matrix family metadata for attention_query_weight, attention_key_weight, attention_value_weight, attention_output_weight, mlp_expansion_weight, and mlp_contraction_weight.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Define each family's dense shape and clean structural axes.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Define explicit head partition metadata for attention families.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Introduce a CompactTrajectory or equivalent materialization adapter.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Keep sheet/model.py requesting semantic family names.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Keep Q/K/V concatenation as a boundary operation for nanoGPT c_attn compatibility.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Implement only legacy CHEBY_SHEET_COL through the new seam during this stage.\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Tests\b0\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Legacy CHEBY_SHEET_COL materialized tensors match the Stage 0 fixture.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - DENSE forward/backward smoke test still passes.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Compact forward/backward smoke test still passes.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Optimizer coverage tests confirm coefficients are included exactly once and basis buffers are excluded.\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Exit gate\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 The new abstraction seam exists and preserves legacy SHEET_COL behaviour. This is the key safety gate.\par

\pard\sa190\sb280\f0\fs29\b 7. Stage 4: CURVE\b0\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Goal\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 Implement the clean depth-only compact preset.\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Coefficient layout\b0\par
\pard\sa180\li360\f1\fs20 C[output_row, input_col, depth_order]\line W_l[o,i] = sum_p C[o,i,p] * D[l,p]\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Work items\b0\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Add curve materialization for all repeated attention and MLP matrix families.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Implement CHEBY_CURVE first.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Add parameter counting and metadata for CURVE coefficient shapes.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Add wrapper support for geometry_preset=curve.\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Tests\b0\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Shape tests for every repeated matrix family.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Direct scalar materialization tests.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Parameter-count tests.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Tiny CPU train-step smoke test.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - CUDA smoke test where available.\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Exit gate\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 CHEBY_CURVE trains for at least one smoke step and records correct metadata.\par

\pard\sa190\sb280\f0\fs29\b 8. Stage 5: MLP_BLOCK\b0\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Goal\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 Implement clean 3D block compaction for MLP matrices while leaving attention on CURVE.\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Applicable families\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 mlp_expansion_weight has shape [4 * n_embd, n_embd].\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 mlp_contraction_weight has shape [n_embd, 4 * n_embd].\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Coefficient layout\b0\par
\pard\sa180\li360\f1\fs20 C[depth_order, row_order, col_order]\line W_l[o,i] = sum_pqr C[p,q,r] * D[l,p] * Row[o,q] * Col[i,r]\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Work items\b0\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Add mlp_block materialization for the two MLP matrix families.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Derive row_order and col_order from actual axis widths. Do not overload one old order field for both axes.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Keep attention_geometry=curve under the MLP_BLOCK preset.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Recheck initialization so materialized MLP weights have expected scale.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Add parameter summaries that separate MLP compact parameters from attention compact parameters.\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Tests\b0\par
