\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Materialize per-input-head attention output slices and assemble the attention output matrix.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Add BLOCK preset expansion to head_aware_block plus mlp_block only after HEAD_AWARE_BLOCK works independently.\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Tests\b0\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Q/K/V role separation tests.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Per-head coefficient shape tests.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - No-basis-over-head tests.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - c_attn packing compatibility tests.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Attention output input-head packing tests.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - BLOCK preset expansion tests.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Tiny CHEBY_BLOCK train-step smoke test.\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Exit gate\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 CHEBY_BLOCK runs and metadata proves that no attention basis crosses a head boundary.\par

\pard\sa190\sb280\f0\fs29\b 10. Stage 7: DCT basis kernel\b0\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Goal\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 Add DCT as the first alternative orthogonal basis family after CHEBY geometries are stable.\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Formula\b0\par
\pard\sa180\li360\f1\fs20 B[n,0] = sqrt(1 / N)\line B[n,k] = sqrt(2 / N) * cos(pi * (n + 0.5) * k / N), for k > 0\line k = 0 .. order - 1\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Work items\b0\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Implement basis_family=dct through the basis-kernel interface.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Record basis_version=dct_ii_orthonormal_v1.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Do not QR DCT unless numerical tests require it.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Enable DCT_CURVE first, then DCT_MLP_BLOCK, then DCT_BLOCK.\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Tests\b0\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - DCT basis shape and Gram-error tests.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - CHEBY/DCT cache separation tests.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - DCT save/resume tests.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - CHEBY/DCT mismatch hard-fail tests.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Tiny smoke train tests for DCT_CURVE, DCT_MLP_BLOCK, and DCT_BLOCK.\par
\pard\sa120\sb170\f0\fs24\b Exit gate\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 DCT works across all accepted presets without changing geometry code outside the basis-kernel interface.\par

